</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F36C1C133619EED5F5D44D7085089183" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="02378412ADF80A1DD2802EA73FFB15E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1914B9808D77A18534C3CB8159E1BC75" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
[Montenegro] Dalmatia mer., Herceg Novi, 80 m, 1929, M. 
<normalizedToken id="3D201A10221BCCC0F9A8394D0114E4A7" originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
(PRM-760604!, holotype).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BC0041231BEF9464A14AC666F8B0A652" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="2AAA411E36101F582B403B88C6771564" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F06D96E2E5694C57F89BDDD414AAB7EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus white to grey, endolithic. Perithecia 0.12-0.26 mm, immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock; ca. 30-40 perithecia/cm2. Involucrellum absent. Exciple ca. 0.4 mm in diam., wall black. Periphysoids ca. 35-50 
<normalizedToken id="41151AD1933823EAD631CF5D7F2F05E8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 mm, branched-anastomosing. Ascospores 0-septate (only few seen), 20-23 
<normalizedToken id="5FC03281691DBD13BA9C2247E215A0DC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-11 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8032A7654A1BB6EE485428747F64735" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph id="6CC409764B8BADAD44D3E26507CA40C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B7CF777E06D30EEC3B16EE8132D8A30" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The spore size given in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation id="F52D6CC4962CA8817303D8EC8A8EC126" author="Servit, M" journalOrPublisher="Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="67 - 115" refId="B48" refString="Servit, M, 1948. The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II. Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca 9: 67 - 115" title="The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II." volume="9" year="1948">
<normalizedToken id="E61A7678F994B13785F5EC28660897CB" originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
1948
</bibRefCitation>
) is 21-25(-32) 
<normalizedToken id="5DC3C03A65B7B92C9453118306D46251" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-13(-15) mm. The species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F5834EE5271BA2178AE17DB1428B36CD" genus="V." lsidName="V. devergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis id="6E556F88B12EB3E4BB20CD9AF4A2D2E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="248D87B0793F0D343C7DEDBD2DC6AE8F" genus="V." lsidName="V. foveolata" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="foveolata">
<emphasis id="B78671072BB4C694C1D1A041F0537E34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. foveolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in smaller spores. 
<taxonomicName id="51EEC45C72762EA74C42E1248CBE745C" authorityName="Nyl., Flora 55: 362" authorityYear="1872" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria devergens" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis id="3F362EE8147CE59564844CDF892E7C52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller exciple (up to 0.35 mm). 
<taxonomicName id="4085B066AD87D3D9768E80F409AA85FE" authorityName="Anzi, Comm. Soc. Critt. Ital. 2 (1): 23" authorityYear="1864" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria caesiopsila" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caesiopsila">
<emphasis id="89F63E3425A44DE045C46EC12D543726" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria caesiopsila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may differ in a smaller exciple and possibly in smaller spores.
</paragraph>
